reviews.review_text: Just look at that {cough, cough} setlist It's a bad one.  No jams to be found, except a little trail off from GDTRFB.  He's Gone goes straight into GDTRFB without any jam whatsoever, unless you count vocal warbling.  That song and Samson at least are played with fire.  Crazy Fingers is always nice, and so is the Wheel, but then you get Black Peter > Around and Around -- yuck!  Haven't heard the first set, just David Lemieux playing the pre-drum second on Sirius (why, David?).  Just playing some songs with high energy and tightness isn't enough when it's the Dead you're talking about.  A generous 3 stars.
